<h2 class='page-intro'>Making CES Green</h2>
<p class="intro">The <a href="https://www.cta.tech" target="_blank">Consumer Technology Association (CTA)</a>&trade;, owner and producer of CES, is committed to making CES greener than ever.

<h3 style="margin-bottom: -5px;"><a href="/CES/media/pdfs/green-guide.pdf" target="_blank"><img alt="2017 CES Green Guide" src="/CES/media/about-images/green-guide-pdf-cover.jpg" style="float: left; margin: auto 20px;" /></a>See the 2017 CES CES Green Guide</h3>

<p>The <i>CES Green Guide </i>provides a self-guided tour of a collection of the CES 2017 green companies and showcases these organizations&rsquo; environmentally-friendly products.&nbsp;</p>

<p>It also highlights the <a href="https://www.cta.tech" target="_blank">Consumer Technology Association</a> (CTA)&trade; initiatives and the work its members are doing to promote energy efficiency, ecycling and sustainable materials management.</p>

<p><strong><a href="/CES/media/pdfs/green-guide.pdf">Download the full guide</a>. (PDF)</strong><br />
<strong><a href="/Show-Floor/CES-Green-Guide.aspx">Take a self-guided Green Tour of CES 2017.</a>&nbsp;&gt;</strong></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><img alt="More than 4.8 tons or steel and 3,000 pounds of aluminum were melted down and recycled." src="/CES/media/about-images/green-metals.jpg" style="float: right; width: 50%; margin-right: 1%; margin-bottom: 0.5em;" /><img alt="We donated show materials to nonprofit organizations." src="/CES/media/about-images/green-show-materials.jpg" style="float: right; width: 50%; margin-right: 1%; margin-bottom: 0.5em;" /></p>

<h3 style="margin-bottom: -5px;">What We&#39;ve Done at CES</h3>

<p>We champion green initiatives that reduce waste and give back to the local community. We work with our general contractor and vendors to make the CES production process more sustainable.</p>

<p>Here is what we accomplished at CES 2016:</p>

<ul>
	<li>More than 1 million square feet of carpet were reused and 330,000 square feet were recycled by our general contractor, Freeman.</li>
	<li>More than 33,000 square feet of magnetic banners were recycled.</li>
	<li>More than 5,660 square feet of vinyl banner materials, used as directional signage on the show floor, were repurposed by Sky Group into tarps, hockey rink liners and outdoor movie screens.</li>
	<li>More than 4.8 tons of steel and 3,000 pounds of aluminum were melted down and recycled.</li>
	<li>Eight trailers of show materials, totaling more than 78,000 pounds, were donated to Habitat for Humanity, Opportunity Village, Goodwill and Teacher Exchange.</li>
	<li>CES press rooms are green with only paperless press kits permitted, saving an estimated 2.5 million pages of printed paper.</li>
</ul>
</p>  

<h3 style="margin-bottom: -5px;">Giving Back</h3>

<p>CTA has a long history of supporting programs in Las Vegas that benefit the local community and environment. We will announce this year&rsquo;s grant recipients at CES 2017.&nbsp;<br />
<br />
<strong>2016 Grant Recipients</strong></p>

<ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
	<li>
